resumes.text: John Doe Phone Number | Email Address | LinkedIn URL | GitHub URL Experience Back-End Developer February 2021 – Present E-Commerce & Warehouse Operations Company Location Withheld • Designed and implemented backend services and algorithmic workflows to optimize warehouse receiving operations, improving packaging and storage efficiency by approximately 50%. • Developed RESTful APIs for task creation, assignment, routing, and status updates, with full audit logging, reducing task processing errors by 30% and enabling real-time reporting for over 500 daily operational tasks. • Built and maintained RESTful APIs using Node.js and AWS Lambda to automate over 20 operational workflows, handling hundreds of production requests per day and saving hundreds of labor hours across a workforce of 300+ warehouse employees. • Developed and optimized complex SQL queries against MySQL databases containing 20M+ records to support operational reporting and real-time decision making. • Implemented and maintained 30+ process automation nodes within a Spring-based workflow engine, enabling reliable execution of business-critical processes across multiple warehouse facilities. • Collaborated with operations and engineering stakeholders to translate warehouse requirements into scalable, production-ready backend systems. Technical Skills Languages: JavaScript, TypeScript, SQL, Python, PHP, Java Backend & Cloud: Node.js, AWS (Lambda, EC2, DynamoDB), RESTful APIs, PM2 Databases & Data: MySQL, SQLite, Snowflake, SQL Server, Data Modeling, Query Optimization Frontend Frameworks: React, Next.js AI & Agents: LLM Tool Use, Streaming Inference, AI Agent Frameworks DevOps & Tooling: Git, npm, Docker, CI/CD Testing & Observability: Jest, Kibana Architecture & Concepts: Microservices, Serverless Architecture, Authentication, Workflow Automation Education Public University City, State Bachelor of Science in Computer Science • Graduated in Honors Program (top 1% of students). • Ranked top 5% in a graduate-level Algorithms course as an undergraduate. Projects Full-Stack Cloud Management Tool | Next.js, TypeScript, AWS SDK v3, AI Agent Framework • Built a full-stack cloud database management GUI with an integrated AI assistant enabling natural language schema explanation, query code generation, and index optimization suggestions directly in the UI. • Designed a multi-tool AI agent with schema introspection, multi-language code generation, and structured optimization analysis grounded in live table data. • Implemented a streaming chat interface with active table context injection for dynamic, context-aware responses. • Implemented full item-level CRUD with bulk operations and structured JSON attribute visualization. Movie Recommendation Web Application | Next.js, TypeScript, Node.js, REST APIs • Built a web application that helps users discover new movies based on films they already enjoy. • Designed an API-driven recommendation flow where users select movies and receive curated suggestions. • Implemented a scalable frontend architecture using Next.js and TypeScript. • Structured the application to allow future expansion for user accounts and social features.

structured.roleSummary: Experienced back-end developer with strong expertise in building scalable RESTful APIs and workflow automation systems for warehouse operations. Demonstrated ability to optimize complex operational processes through algorithmic solutions and cloud-based microservices, resulting in significant efficiency gains and cost savings. Proficient in full-stack development with a focus on backend systems, databases, and AI integration.

Implemented and maintained process automation nodes within Spring-based workflow engine
Collaborated with stakeholders to translate requirements into scalable backend systems

Designed multi-tool AI agents with schema introspection and code generation capabilities
Implemented streaming chat interfaces with context-aware responses
Developed web applications with API-driven architecture and scalable frontend design
